    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">One knows perfectly well that on these formal occasions it is the right of leaders of political parties to state their party's point of view. Rather than have an Adjournment, I gave my consent to this, and I take full responsibility for it. Realising that the Guillo- <span id="374" class="column-number" data-column-number="374"></span> tine has to fall at 5.30 and that, therefore, there is little time for discussion on the Steel Bill, I thought this was the quickest way out: that statements should be made by the responsible leaders of the Opposition parties. It is not for me to tell them how long or how short they should be.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-00ad7640-dc01-4db0-935f-f90d72d1ac9a" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1949-04-28/debates/9613905e-dffb-48b2-86c7-8ca62dc8ed6e/India(CommonwealthRelations)#contribution-00ad7640-dc01-4db0-935f-f90d72d1ac9a">
